Let $x$ be the number of gallons the tank holds when it is full.  Then $\frac{7}{8}x$ is the number of gallons in the tank when it is $\frac{7}{8}$ full.  After $12$ gallons have been used, the tank is half full, so $\frac{1}{2}x$ is the number of gallons in the tank at this point.  We can set up the following equation:

$$\frac{7}{8}x-12=\frac{1}{2}x$$

Solving for $x$, we get:

\begin{align*}
\frac{7}{8}x-\frac{1}{2}x&=12\\
\Rightarrow\qquad\frac{3}{8}x&=12\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x&=\frac{12\cdot8}{3}=\boxed{32}
\end{align*}
Final Answer: The final answer is 32. I hope it is correct.

